.TH BWHO 1 "2026-06-29" "smartmet-monitor" "SmartMet Server"
.SH NAME
bwho \- top productions by the injected who= query parameter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bwho
.RI [ \-n\  N ]
.RI [ \-s\  reqs|ms|mb|err ]
.RI [ LOG-FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bwho
groups access\-log entries by the value of the
.B who=<production>
query\-string parameter that operators inject to attribute load to
specific productions, and prints the top
.B N
values sorted by the chosen metric. Requests with no
.B who=
parameter are collected into a single
.B (none)
bucket so unattributed load stays visible. Each row shows request
count, mean latency, the 4xx and 5xx error rates, total bandwidth in
MB, and a horizontal bar scaled to the leading metric.
.PP
This is an entity view: rows are ranked by load and there is no time
axis. To inspect one production over time, grep it out and pipe to
.BR bstat (1):
.PP
.RS
.EX
grep 'who=ecmwf_hres' access.log | bstat \-i 10m
.EE
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n \ N
Number of who= values to show. Default
.BR 30 .
.TP
.BI \-s \ SORT
Sort column. One of
.BR reqs ,\  ms ,\  mb ,\  err
(err = 4xx+5xx error count). Default
.BR ms .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bstat (1),
.BR bchart (1),
.BR burls (1),
.BR bstatus (1),
.BR bkeys (1),
.BR bip (1),
.BR smtop (1)
